<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-03-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-03-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="353" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Clay</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 191.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,
                                        Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-03-06"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 6, 1866.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have received with great satisfaction
                            your despatch No. 99, of the 6th of February, and its accompanying
                            report of the proceedings at the banquet given by the merchants of
                            Moscow to the American legation and the mayor of that city.</p>
                        <p>The details of this feast have been already indirectly published, and
                            they have excited an influence favorable to the present growth of
                            friendship towards Russia, which is even now a unanimous sentiment of
                            the American people.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Cassius M. Clay</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>